 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Sr Research Scientist- Materials Corning 675 reviews Painted Post, NY Corning 675 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Location:  Painted Post, NY, US, 14830
 Company:  Corning
 Requisition Number: 47373 
 
 Corning is one of the world’s leading innovators in materials science. For more than 160 years, Corning has applied its unparalleled expertise in specialty glass, ceramics, and optical physics to develop products that have created new industries and transformed people’s lives. 
 
At Corning, our growth is fueled by a commitment to innovation. We succeed through sustained investment in research & development, a unique combination of material and process innovation, and close collaboration with customers to solve tough technology challenges. We are a four-time National Medal of Technology winner thanks to our technology leadership and R&D environment, which attract and enable the best scientific minds in the world. This pipeline of talent has brought life-changing innovation to your fingertips for more than 160 years. 
 
 Scope of Position (i.e. projects involved with and role within group): Primary function is to support research and development of materials by developing and enabling material characterization. The individual will specifically support the development of glass property measurements relating to liquidus and viscosity techniques. The individual must have a solid and sound technical background in Geology, Material Science or Glass Science with extensive knowledge of crystal phases. Additionally, the individual is expected to have hands-on experience with identifying crystal phases. In this role, the person will develop techniques and conduct experiments to determine the liquidus and viscosity properties of glass and glass ceramics. Some glass science and glass ceramics knowledge will be necessary. The individual is also expected to work with other scientists to develop other new thermo-physical methods for non-routine measurements or processes. 
 Day to Day Responsibilities:
 Work with a cross functional lab team in a leading role to develop new methods for measuring liquidus and viscosity properties.
 Refine and extend existing concepts or proposed new concepts for measurement improvement
 Demonstrate feasibility of approach selected and reduce to practice for deployment
 Lead and provide hands-on measurement of technique developed
 Develop and manage testing plans
 Collaborating with teams on ideation and problem solving
 Support Thermo-physical lab as technical SME to interface with customers
 Conduct experiments to gain fundamental knowledge and address technical challenges
 Perform data analysis and interpretation
 Make recommendations to projects to improve functional performance of materials and processes as appropriate
 Develop new intellectual property 
 Travel requirements (please note if international): Variable but expectation is <15%
 Hours of work/work schedule/flex-time: Hours of work/work schedule/flex-time: 40+ hours per week w/ flex time 
 Education and Experience (minimum required for consideration):
 Required Education:
 At least a Master’s/PhD in Geology or Material Science or Glass Science Required Years and Area of Experience: Some experience is desired, but not necessary 
 Required Skills (These are skills that candidates must possess):
 Technical matter expert in area of crystal phase identification in various materials including glass melts, glass ceramic, & ceramics
 Some knowledges of glass science and glass ceramics
 Hands-on technical aptitude with experience using polarization microscopes
 Knowledgeable about other test methods such as XRD, Raman, etc., used in crystalline material characterization
 Has an affinity for working with computers and automation
 Strong communication skills and comfort in the facilitation of technical personnel
 Strong attention to detail, rigorous execution, and data accuracy
 Able to manage multiple priorities at once
 Strong logistical skills
 Able to work with data and communicate results from data 
 Desired Skills (these are the skills that would be nice for candidates to possess):
 Some hands-on experience in Liquidus properties measurement
 Interested in Machine Learning and artificial intelligence
 Mechanical and electrical aptitude
 Ability to define DOEs and perform statistical analyses
 Industry experience
 Customer facing interaction and communication skills/experience 
 Soft Skills (Communication/Team/Leadership):
 Strong organization skills
 Strong communication skills – verbal and written
 Ability to interact with all levels within the organization
 Ability to work with small to medium sized cross-functional technical teams
 Team player and flexible 
 
